<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gamorrah1</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>Hey gang, I could use some advice on upgrading.  <BR> <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76327" TARGET=_blank>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76327</A> <P>The spots i was especially looking at were Back/Belt.  Chest too, but i'm still dreaming of getting Skyshrine  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I have a little over 20k to spend.<P>I was debating...get a Heiro Cloak for Back.  That would set me back between 12-15k tho.  Any other suggestions?  I'm not in a guild atm, so i wont be farming any high level mobs any time soon.<P>Would you recommend a Heiro Cloak or Lodi Shield for back?<P>Gam<BR>59 Templar<BR>Zeb</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shortyrez</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Join a guild and get Kael/Skyshrine armor.  Seriously...<P>As far as spending 20k, here's how I think you would best benefit.<P>Without maxxed wis, I would go with this cloak:  Acryllia studded cloak 7ac 3str 5dex 10wis.  Should only cost 2-3k and will allow you to spend money on other items too.  Upgrade one of your rings to Shadel Bandit Ring 6ac 55hp 55mana 5svc 10svd, also about 2-3k.  Then personally I would use the rest for an Emerald Dragonscale Tunic 22ac 20wis 10cha 10svm 10svd, down to about 12k on my server.<P>Until you get around 230 wis (KEI pushes you to cap then), you will notice most improvement in upgrading wisdom.  Please don't ever buy a Lodi Shield.  It's the biggest piece of crap item in the high end game.<P>Couple other free things you could do for gear.  If you are on CoV faction, do the Benevolence quest in WW.  Takes 6 people about 20 mins including travel time as long as the scout is up.  You get Talisman of Benevolence 7ac 15wis 38hp 55mana 12svm 12svc range slot item.  Possibly find a larger guild and offer to help them if you see them going to kill the Rhags.  First two rhags have to die for Arch Lich to spawn, and the hammer from first Rhag (Righteousness 20dmg/22dly 1hb 10str 5sta 10wis 10sv m/f/c 25hp 25mana) is often rotting now.  I know there are a few guilds out there that don't mind tag alongs looting stuff if it would rot anyway.  Maybe make some friends and find a future guild that way too =)<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Magada</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heiro cloak is wonderful for the back, Dain Frostweavers Cloak is also very good but rarely sold and much more expensive.<P>As a level 59 cleric I currently am wearing heirophant</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
